               106                  Ke\nContalner Nos. MSCU3614570\n|    Seal Nos,      702296\n180 CARTONS       FROZEN BONE IN BEEF *S* BACK RIBS                   322,800     3921.800\nEst           235\n108 CARTONS         FROZEN BONE IN BEEF *S* BACK RIBS                      2174.650      2212.450\nEst    384\n71 CARTONS       FROZEN BONE IN BEEF *S* BACK RIBS                   1679.150     1704 .000\nEst                 4\n184 CARTONS       FROZEN SONE IN BEEF *A* BACK RIBS Est     235      3879.350     39680.550\n146 CARTONS         FROZEN BONE IN BEEF *A* BACK RIBS Est      384        3136.856      3187.950\n88 CARTONS         FROZEN BONE IN BEEF *A* BACK RIBS Est        4        1970.256      2000.950\nTOTALS                        777 CARTONS                                                              16662.950    17007.700\nThe above products have not been produced using products derived from ruminant animals from the following\ncountries: Albania, Austria, Belgium, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Brazil, Bulgaria, Canada, Croatia, Czech Republic,\nDenmark, Finland, France, Germany, Greece, Hungary, Ireland, Israel, Italy, Japan, Liechtenstein, Luxembourg,\nMacedonia, Montenegro, Netherlands, Norway, Poland, Portugal, Romania, Serbia, Slovakia, Slovenia, Spain, Sweden,\nSwitzerland, UK or USA.\nSlaughter Dates 4-FEB-2025 TO 21-JUN-202S5 Production Dates 5-FEB-2025 TO 23-JUN-2025\nTHE CONSIGNMENT WAS PRESENTED FOR EXPORT ON 27TH JUNE 2025\nI hereby certify in respect of the abovementioned goods that:\nAustralia has been free, for the past one year, from fool and mouth disease, classical swinc fever, for the past two ycars, from vesicular stomatitis, swine vesicular disease,\ntinderpest, contagious bovine pleuropnetmania, bovine brucellosis, Theileriosis (Theileria parva/T, annulata), Aujeszky’s disease, porcine enterovirus encephalomyclitis,\nmaedi-visna, enzootic abortion of ewes, porcine reproductive and respiratory syndrome and porcine transraissible gastro-enteritis (TGE); for the past three yeary, from\npeste des petits ruminants, lumpy skin disease, sheep pox and Afncan swine fever, for the past four years, from Rift Valley fever; and for the last five years, from bovine\nSpongiform encephalopathy and scrapie. Australia does not vaccinate against the above diseases. The country disease-free status and vaccination attestations made above\nare only applicable to susceptible species. The above mentioned meat or meat products were produced from animals which received ante-mortem and post-morlem\ngoverment veterinary inspection, The animals from which the products were derived were either bom and raised in Austalia, or have been raised in Australia for more\nthan 3 months prior to export. Only clean, new bags, wrappers and packaging were used in the preparation of this consignment. The products were produced, processed,\nstored and transported in such a way as to prevent contamination with communicable disease pathogens. The meat or meat products were produced under programs which\nminimize harmful residues and pathagenic microorganisms. They liave uot been treated with irradiation or tenderizers, nor has any harmful ingredient been used im their\npreparation, They are suilabic in cvery way for human consumption.                                                                                              ‘Seal\na ats GO\nDated at       BRISBANE        in the State of QUEENSLAND                                                                                                AS             >\ni                      ‘te\nthis 3RD DAY OF JULY 2025                                                                 2      중\n주             hig            ~\n4\n2                                                                                                                                                                                                 shy, QUST A ee\nStewart Lowden BVSe                                                              3660\neS So a —         ————————ee—r—r—r—r—————————                        4g         urd\nSignature Veterinary Officer, Department of                           Printed Naine                                                                                                      ricult\nAgriculture, Fisheries and Forestry\n61588. - 10:22','## PDF 문서 요약\n\n**1. 전체 내용 요약:**\n\n본 문서는 JBS Australia Pty Limited이 MSC Jubilee IX호 선박을 이용하여 브리스바(Brisbane)에서 부산(Busan) 및 광주(Gwangju)로 운송되는 냉동 뼈 다리 (Frozen Bone in Beef) 화물의 선하증권(Bill of Lading)입니다. 화물은 40피트 컨테이너 777개로 구성되며, 총 무게는 17,007.700kg, 부피는 27,000cu.m.이며, 운송료는 선박 회사의 규정에 따라 지불되고 있습니다. 본 선하증권은 MSC Korea Limited가 부산 항구에서 처리하며, 수령인(Consignee)은 Shinhan Bank Seoul입니다.\n\n**2. 주요 키워드:**\n\n*   **선하증권 (Bill of Lading):** 화물 운송 계약의 기본 서류\n*   **MSC Jubilee IX:** 화물을 운송하는 선박명\n*   **JBS Australia:** 화물을 수출하는 회사\n*   **냉동 뼈 다리 (Frozen Bone in Beef):** 화물 종류\n*   **컨테이너 운송 (Container Shipping):** 화물 운송 방식\n\n**3. 중요 포인트:**\n\n*   **수령인:** Shinhan Bank Seoul\n*   **화물:** 냉동 뼈 다리 (Frozen Bone in Beef) - 40피트 컨테이너 777개\n*   **운송선사:** MSC Korea Limited (부산 항구 담당)\n*   **운송항구:** 부산 (Busan), 광주 (Gwangju)\n*   **운송료:** 선박 회사의 규정에 따라 지불 (다양한 통화로 금액 명시)\n*   **운송 조건:** Freight Prepaid (운임 선불), Carrier Security Fee, Documentation Fee 등 포함','gemma3:latest',18159,'2026-03-16 11:05:53','2026-03-16 11:07:00',16,NULL,NULL,NULL,29.320,61.832,NULL,1124514,2,2,'기타',0,NULL,1,'tesseract'),
