f or beef products were derived fram cattle that were slaughtered in meat establishments (slaughterhouses) certified by the U.S.\ngovernment as eligible to export beef and beef products lo Korea and 113! passed ante-mortem and post-mortem inspection conducted by USDA\n\n:         inspection personnel under the supervision of the resident USDA veterinarian.\n\n4. The beef or beef products were derived from cattle that were not subjected 10 a stunning process, prior to slaughter, with a device injecting\ncampressed air or gas inlo the crania! cavity, or to a pithing process.\n\n5. The beef or beef products were produced and handled in 2 manner as to prevent contamination from SRMs, mechanically separated meat derived\nfrom beef, or from advanced meal recovery products from 116 skull and vertebral calumn of cattle 30 months of age and over at the time of\nslaughter, in accardance with FSIS regulations.\n\n6. Based on the U.S. regulations and guidelines, the beef or beef producis are free of harmful residues. The beef or beef products were produced\naccording lo the U. S. Pathogen Reduction/HACCP Systems Regulation. The use of irradiation/UV treatment and tenderizers complies with U.S.\nregulations.\n\n7. Sanitary packaging material was used to package the beef or beef products.\n\n8. The processing and storage of the beef and beef products were handled in such a manner as 10 prevent contamination by communicable animal\ndisease pathogens.                                                                                                        ：\n\nPRINTED NAME OF FSIS VETERINARIAN                                         TITLE\n\nPON tery ~\n\nSAMERONM CAROYY                                              DOYS 13-24                    ky        %,\n= =                                                                                                                    fe             a\nSIGNATURE                                                                                              ‘DATE                         a   &   더\n;    08/18/2025    Oe Wt SY\n\nDY /5 2          |         SS\n\nTHE FOLLOWING SECTION TO BE COMPLETED BY EXPORTER/SHIPPER                                       :\n\n“NAME OF SHIPPING PORT                         | NAME OF VESSEL (OR FLIGHT)                    SHIPPING DATE\n\n| Oakland. ㄴㄴ. owe FRomtiewm 1. e- 29-2025) .. ..\n\n|                                                         | CERTIFY THAT THE ABOVE INFORMATION iS TRUE.\n\n~ SIGNATURE OF EXPORTER/SHIPPER                                            TYPED (or printed) NAME OF EXPORTER/SHIPPER AND TITLE\n\nFSIS FORM 930            8/2008)\n\nORIGINAL','## PDF 문서 요약\n\n**1. 전체 내용 요약 (3~5 문장)**\n\n본 문서는 선하 증서(Bill of Lading)로서, KEB HANA Bank의 위탁품(냉동 쇠고기)을 SHIPPERJEXPORTER(SWIFT BERF COMPANY)에서 DENVER(미국)의 GRREELEY로 운송하는 내용을 담고 있습니다. 컨테이너 종류, 운송 조건, 화물 가치, 운임 등 상세 정보가 기재되어 있으며, 운송 당사자 간의 책임 범위 및 절차에 대한 조항이 포함되어 있습니다. 또한, 비상 연락처 및 관련 정보가 함께 제공됩니다.\n\n**2. 주요 키워드 (5개 이하)**\n\n*   선하 증서 (Bill of Lading)\n*   냉동 쇠고기 (Frozen Beef)\n*   컨테이너 (Container)\n*   운임 (Freight)\n*   금액 (USD)\n\n**3. 중요 포인트 (3~5가지)**\n\n*   **운송 조건:** 컨테이너 종류 및 수량, 운송 온도, 운송 지역 등의 구체적인 정보가 명시되어 있습니다.\n*   **화물 가치:** 화물 가치가 명시되어 있으며, Carrier는 Merchant의 허위 보고에 대해 책임지지 않음을 강조하고 있습니다.\n*   **운임 지불:** 운임 지불 방식 (Pre-carriage, Destination Charge) 및 관련 금액이 상세히 기재되어 있습니다.\n*   **책임 범위:** Carrier의 책임 범위를 명확히 규정하여, 화물의 손실 또는 지연에 대한 Carrier의 책임을 제한하고 있습니다.\n*   **추가 정보:** 운송 관련 추가 조건 및 절차 (e.g., origin fees, electronic release systems)가 함께 제공됩니다.\n\n---\n\n**참고:** 문서 내용은 복잡하고 전문적인 용어가 많으므로, 이 요약이 완벽한 이해를 제공하지 못할 수 있습니다. 필요하다면 관련 전문 지식을 활용하여 추가적인 확인이 필요합니다.','gemma3:latest',16413,'2026-03-16 11:36:00','2026-03-16 11:36:56',16,NULL,NULL,NULL,39.266,49.146,NULL,1638614,4,4,'기타',0,NULL,1,'tesseract');
